editorialSummary.text: Sophisticated hotel offering restaurants, a chic spa & a fitness center, plus sea views.

text.text:
We are now staying in the Tolip Hotel. We took a "family room" which is two big rooms; one room with a king size bed while the other has two large beds. The rooms; each has a balcony overlooking the swimming pool and a nice view to the sea. The rooms are clean as well as the bathroom, and smell nice

Everyone was hospitable but I want to specially thank the young lady at the reception desk, Sarah Maurice as she was very nice and exceptionally helpful.

We were quickly answered when we phoned the room service and we were promptly given what we asked for.

The breakfast was nice and there is a huge choice of food and drinks.

The only thing I may remark on is that the speed of the room internet was on the slow side and I chose to use my mobile data. I hope this issue can be improved.

I highly recommend this hotel and definitely would come again.

text.text:
I recently stayed at your hotel, and I wanted to share my feedback on the experience. Overall, I found the breakfast and facilities to be good, and the room itself was comfortable. However, I encountered a significant issue that impacted the quality of my stay.

The lack of noise cancellation in the windows made it extremely noisy in my room, particularly as I had booked a sea-facing room. The noise levels made it very difficult to sleep, and I eventually had to use earplugs to get any rest. When I raised this concern with the receptionist, I was informed that the hotel is aware of this issue and that there was supposedly a plan to replace the windows. However, it appears that this plan has not been implemented yet.

For a hotel that charges premium prices, I strongly urge you to prioritize upgrading your rooms and addressing this problem. Guests should be able to enjoy their stay in comfort, especially in a hotel of your standard and reputation.

Thank you for taking the time to consider my feedback. I hope that future guests will benefit from improvements in this area.

text.text:
My stay at the Four Seasons Hotel Alexandria was nothing short of exceptional. From the moment I arrived, the staff provided warm and attentive service, ensuring every detail was perfect. The rooms are spacious, elegantly designed, and offer breathtaking views of the Mediterranean.

One of the hotel’s great advantages is its prime location, right next to San Stefano Mall, making shopping and dining incredibly convenient. The dining options within the hotel are also outstanding, especially the seafood restaurant, which serves fresh, flavorful dishes with a stunning seaside ambiance.

The spa and wellness facilities are top-notch, offering a truly relaxing experience. Whether for business or leisure, this hotel exceeds expectations in every way. Highly recommended for anyone looking for luxury and comfort in Alexandria!

text.text:
A fantastic, clean, and luxurious location. It has an old timey look, but in an elegant and professionally maintained way. Everyone was so kind, courteous, and professional. They clean your room like 2-3 times a day, it felt like every time I left (even for a short while), they would go in and freshen everything up.

The breakfast spread is okay. They let the food sit out for awhile so it loses its flavor and quality relatively quickly. There’s a decent amount of options.

The actual restaurants are great, I ate here a couple times during my stay and it was the best food I had during my entire trip.

The gym, sad to say, is awful. It’s poorly set up, not well maintained, and there are not a lot of options. If keeping up with fitness is important to you on your trip, this is not the place.

Other than that- a wonderful experience overall!

text.text:
I recently had the opportunity to stay at the Four Seasons Hotel in Alexandria, Egypt, and I wanted to share my experience. Overall, the hotel has a lot to offer, but there were some aspects that left me with mixed feelings.

Cleanliness and Service: 5/5
First and foremost, the cleanliness of the hotel was impeccable. From the lobby to the guest rooms, everything was spotless, which is always a top priority for me when traveling. The service was another highlight; the staff was incredibly attentive and went above and beyond to ensure my stay was comfortable. They were friendly, professional, and always willing to assist with any requests.

Food: 5/5
The dining options at the Four Seasons were exceptional. The food was delicious, with a variety of local and international dishes that catered to different tastes. Every meal I had was a delight, showcasing the culinary creativity and quality that the hotel is known for.

Value for Money: 2/5
However, I must mention that the price of my stay was quite steep. I paid around $1000 for one night, which I felt was excessive, especially considering it wasn't the peak season. While I appreciate the luxury experience, the cost seemed disproportionate to the amenities provided.

Room Amenities: 2/5
Additionally, I found the bathroom amenities lacking. Essential items like toothbrushes and toothpaste were not provided, which is something I would expect from a hotel of this caliber. It’s the small details that can make a big difference in the overall experience.

Overall Impression: 3/5
In summary, the Four Seasons Hotel in Alexandria is a beautiful property with excellent service and fantastic food. However, the high price point and the lack of certain basic amenities may give potential guests pause. If you're looking for a luxurious getaway and don't mind the cost, this hotel could be a wonderful choice, but it's important to weigh the value against what is offered.

I would recommend the hotel, but with the caveat to prepare for the premium pricing and to manage expectations regarding room amenities.

text.text:
Disappointing Stay at Hilton Green Plaza**

I recently had my worst hotel experience at Hilton Green Plaza. Upon arrival, I was assigned a room that was far from the main areas and overlooked the cinema. The noise from the outside mall was unbearable, prompting me to request a room change.

I moved to one of the newly renovated rooms, but unfortunately, my troubles continued. A large group from a Moroccan team occupied many of the rooms and created an incredible amount of noise, partying until 2:00 AM. To make matters worse, at 6:00 AM, they had speakers blasting music in the corridors, dancing and shouting.

Despite my complaints, the hotel staff did nothing to address the situation. I ended up having a terrible night and left feeling extremely dissatisfied with my stay .
Additionally I found lamps in the bathroom are not working only two was working the rest need to be change and one inside the room which added to over all discomfort . I expected better from Hilton
Hilton green plaza never again

I stayed in the Hilton Green Plaza Hotel for 3 weeks in Nov-Dec ‘24.

I must say, I thoroughly enjoyed my time in the hotel for all these 3 weeks. I felt like it was my 2nd home, away from home, and have got very good memories of my stay.

I would like to appreciate a few members of the hotel, whose help I cherished during my stay:
- Mr Wakil, Mr Ramadan and Mr Mahmoud in the Ginger and Masala Restaurants. They took our dinner orders, and made sure they prepared excellent tasty Indian dishes for us on a daily basis.
- Ms Salma, Ms. Iram, the elder gentleman preparing Omelettes and the sweet old lady preparing delicious Falafels for us in the breakfast table
- The front desk staff, whom I asked million times for help in providing me additional room cards when my digital key was not working!
- The room service folks who helped in keeping my room clean, taking care of daily laundry
- The security guards who always welcomed us with their ever smiling faces
- Lastly, I am sure I must have missed some names inadvertently. I may not have remembered all the names, but their faces are all there in my memory.

text.text:
El Mahrousa Hotel – A Hidden Gem in Alexandria

I had the pleasure of staying at El Mahrousa Hotel in Alexandria, and I must say, it exceeded my expectations in every way. Situated right on the Mediterranean coast, the hotel offers breathtaking sea views and a prime location that makes exploring Alexandria a breeze.

The rooms were spacious, clean, and well-maintained, with a touch of classic elegance that reflects the city's rich history. Waking up to the sound of the waves and enjoying a morning coffee on the balcony was truly a highlight of my stay.

The staff at El Mahrousa deserve special mention for their exceptional hospitality. From the moment I arrived, they went above and beyond to ensure my comfort. Whether it was providing local recommendations or accommodating special requests, they were always friendly and professional.

The hotel's restaurant serves a variety of delicious dishes, blending traditional Egyptian flavors with international cuisine. The seafood options were particularly outstanding, and the dining experience was enhanced by the serene ambiance of the restaurant.

Another noteworthy feature is the hotel's proximity to key attractions such as the Alexandria Library, Qaitbay Citadel, and Montazah Palace. It’s perfect for both leisure and business travelers who want convenience and comfort.

Overall, El Mahrousa Hotel is a fantastic choice for anyone visiting Alexandria. It combines excellent service, stunning views, and a welcoming atmosphere to create a memorable experience. I can’t wait to return and would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a place to stay in this beautiful city!
